<subSubSection id="C8A719587FF741FB83F1636A2E4D369B" pageId="0" pageNumber="83231" type="notes">
<paragraph id="C7AF8F4DCA7307D593929719F3E432D3" pageId="0" pageNumber="83231">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0EC5518D901DCAC208C4706EC8B3A6BC" pageId="0" pageNumber="83231">
First record for Bulgaria. 
<emphasis id="80F929B97E05591EA61037046700C3BD" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83231">Southern Black Sea coast</emphasis>
: Sinemorec vill., the mouth of Veleka River, at light, near a marsh, 14.viii.2010, 1♂. Detailed occurrence data: 
<bibRefCitation id="83E37775DC7257BABEF7DBFF16D0F362" author="Gjonov, I." journalOrPublisher="Annals of the Upper Silesian Museum in Bytom. Entomology" pageId="0" pageNumber="83231" refId="B7727581" refString="Gjonov, I., 2022. new_fulgoromorpha_records_bulgaria_2022. In: Biodiversity Data Journal. Occurrence dataset." title="new _ fulgoromorpha _ records _ bulgaria _ 2022" volumeTitle="Biodiversity Data Journal. Occurrence dataset." year="2022">Gjonov (2022)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D3CBFFE3DF08BA47784090B28159B689" pageId="0" pageNumber="83231">
<emphasis id="EB135D624BB2F38B3A50FC40529F9CFD" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83231">Red Lists</emphasis>
: No assessment.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="32BFA7155FD76F36B11B6CCC3F580154" pageId="0" pageNumber="83231">
<emphasis id="376CA3D182A09D40CE97A108E07E0F4A" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83231">Host plant</emphasis>
: There are no literature data. Although the specimen was collected in light, it is assumed that it came from the nearest 
<taxonomicName id="D1C44DD5129C1D91DD9D5F0BE7624904" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Phragmites" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Phragmites australis" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="83231" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="australis">
<emphasis id="8B21E077A26A152A45C3CF3CD9487CE2" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83231">Phragmites australis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Cav.) Trin. ex Steud. plantation, the typical host-plant for 
<taxonomicName id="1CC468BCAC8974ED341FAB6B07561ECB" authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1789" class="Insecta" family="Delphacidae" genus="Delphax" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Delphax" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="83231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="FA68BC013E0C8BAE084B26E72B3ADE46" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83231">Delphax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species (
<bibRefCitation id="86D8396E14CA5141C4A130EA4366C851" author="Nickel, H." journalOrPublisher="Pensoft Publishers, Sofia-Moscow Goecke &amp; Evers, Keltern" pageId="0" pageNumber="83231" refId="B7833465" refString="Nickel, H., 2003. The Leafhoppers and Planthoppers of Germany (Homoptera, Auchenorrhyncha): Patterns and strategies in a highly diverse group of phytophagous insects. Pensoft Publishers, Sofia-Moscow Goecke &amp; Evers, Keltern" title="The Leafhoppers and Planthoppers of Germany (Homoptera, Auchenorrhyncha): Patterns and strategies in a highly diverse group of phytophagous insects" year="2003">Nickel 2003b</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
